tasks.description:
Build the KPI widget renderer displaying a numeric value with optional delta indicator and unit prefix/suffix.

Files to create:
- `apps/admin/src/components/dashboards/widgets/KpiWidget.tsx`

Component interface (AC-7):
```typescript
interface KpiWidgetProps {
  value: number;
  label: string;
  delta?: { direction: 'up' | 'down' | 'neutral'; value: number; unit?: string };
  prefix?: string;
  suffix?: string;
  isLoading?: boolean;
  error?: Error | null;
}
```

Acceptance criteria (AC-6, AC-7, AC-12):
- Displays value prominently with optional prefix/suffix
- Delta shows up/down icon with value and optional unit
- Loading state shows skeleton (from T-028)
- Error state shows red callout (from T-028)

Test requirements:
- Unit test: renders value + prefix + suffix correctly
- Unit test: renders up delta with correct icon
- Unit test: renders down delta with correct icon
- Unit test: renders loading skeleton when `isLoading=true`

Build the list widget renderer displaying top-N items with optional per-item action button or link.

Files to create:
- `apps/admin/src/components/dashboards/widgets/ListWidget.tsx`

Component interface (AC-8):
```typescript
interface ListWidgetItem {
  id: string;
  label: string;
  subLabel?: string;
  badge?: string;
}
interface ListWidgetProps {
  items: ListWidgetItem[];
  actionPerItem?: { label: string; href: (item: ListWidgetItem) => string } | 
                  { label: string; onClick: (item: ListWidgetItem) => void };
  isLoading?: boolean;
  error?: Error | null;
  emptyState?: { message: string };
}
```

Acceptance criteria (AC-6, AC-8, AC-12):
- Renders item list with label, optional subLabel, optional badge
- Per-item action rendered as button or link per config type
- Loading skeleton from T-028
- Empty state from `config.emptyState` message

Test requirements:
- Unit test: renders list of items correctly
- Unit test: action button renders and calls onClick
- Unit test: action link renders with correct href
- Unit test: empty state renders when items=[]
- Unit test: loading state renders skeleton

Build the chart widget renderer supporting line, bar, and area chart types.

Files to create:
- `apps/admin/src/components/dashboards/widgets/ChartWidget.tsx`
- Uses a charting library already present in the admin app (check for recharts or similar in package.json before adding a new dep)

Component interface (AC-9):
```typescript
interface ChartDataPoint { label: string; value: number; }
interface ChartWidgetProps {
  data: ChartDataPoint[];
  chartType: 'line' | 'bar' | 'area';
  xAxisLabel?: string;
  yAxisLabel?: string;
  isLoading?: boolean;
  error?: Error | null;
}
```

Acceptance criteria (AC-6, AC-9, AC-12):
- Renders line chart when `chartType='line'`
- Renders bar chart when `chartType='bar'`
- Renders area chart when `chartType='area'`
- Loading skeleton from T-028
- Error callout from T-028
- Responsive sizing (fills card width)

Test requirements:
- Unit test: renders without error for each chartType
- Unit test: renders loading state when `isLoading=true`
- Unit test: data-point count matches props.data.length

Build the checklist widget renderer with dynamic items sourced from a loaded entity object, a visual completeness indicator, and an accommodation selector dropdown for HOST card D multi-listing behavior.

Files to create:
- `apps/admin/src/components/dashboards/widgets/ChecklistWidget.tsx`

Component interface (AC-10, AC-15):
```typescript
interface ChecklistItem { key: string; label: string; completed: boolean; }
interface ChecklistWidgetProps {
  items: ChecklistItem[];
  completenessPercent: number;   // 0-100
  selector?: {                    // Only for HOST card D with multiple listings
    options: { id: string; label: string }[];
    selectedId: string;
    onSelect: (id: string) => void;
  };
  isLoading?: boolean;
  error?: Error | null;
}
```

Acceptance criteria (AC-6, AC-10, AC-12, AC-15):
- Renders checklist items with visual completed/incomplete state
- Shows completeness percentage indicator (e.g., '4/6 complete')
- When `selector` prop present, renders accommodation dropdown; selecting updates displayed checklist
- Loading/error states from T-028

Test requirements (AC-15):
- Unit test: renders all items with correct completed state
- Unit test: completeness indicator shows correct fraction
- Unit test: selecting different accommodation from dropdown triggers `onSelect` callback
- Unit test: renders without selector when prop is absent

Build the status widget renderer for health/badge cards (subscription status, system health, maintenance mode).

Files to create:
- `apps/admin/src/components/dashboards/widgets/StatusWidget.tsx`

Component interface:
```typescript
type StatusLevel = 'healthy' | 'warning' | 'critical' | 'unknown';
interface StatusItem { label: string; status: StatusLevel; detail?: string; }
interface StatusWidgetProps {
  items: StatusItem[];
  isLoading?: boolean;
  error?: Error | null;
}
```

Acceptance criteria (AC-6, AC-12):
- Each status item renders a color-coded badge (healthy=green, warning=amber, critical=red, unknown=gray)
- Uses semantic design tokens from `@repo/design-tokens` (SPEC-153)
- Loading/error states from T-028
- Visually consistent with other widget types (same card padding, same header style)

Test requirements:
- Unit test: renders all four status levels with correct badge colors/classes
- Unit test: loading state renders skeleton
- Unit test: multiple status items render independently
